Definition at line 297 of file ros_opencl.cpp.

sensor_msgs::PointCloud2 ros_opencl::ROS_OpenCL::process ( const sensor_msgs::PointCloud2 &  msg)

The function that initiates kernel processing.

It uses a read/write buffer to send and receive data from the kernel. The global work size used by default, matches the size of the pointcloud's data vector. The size of the read/write buffer is typeof(char) * <data vector size>. The data sent to the kernel is a vector of chars (bytes).

Parameters
msgThe sensor_msgs::PointCloud2 message to be processed.
Returns
A copy of the processed input.

Definition at line 305 of file ros_opencl.cpp.

void ros_opencl::ROS_OpenCL::process ( sensor_msgs::PointCloud2::Ptr  msg)

The function that initiates kernel processing.

It uses a read/write buffer to send and receive data from the kernel. The global work size used by default, matches the size of the pointcloud's data vector. The size of the read/write buffer is typeof(char) * <data vector size>. The data sent to the kernel is a vector of chars (bytes). Changes are overwritten on the input data.

Parameters
msgThe sensor_msgs::PointCloud2 message to be processed.

Definition at line 466 of file ros_opencl.cpp.

std::vector< float > ros_opencl::ROS_OpenCL::process ( const std::vector< float >  v,
const ROS_OpenCL_Params *  params = NULL 
)

The function that initiates kernel processing.

It uses a read/write buffer to send and receive data from the kernel. The global work size used by default, matches the size of the input vector. The size of the read/write buffer is typeof(float) * <input vector size>

Parameters
vThe input data.
paramsoptional A ROS_OpenCL_Params object that includes the following params:
  • global_work_size: A vector of size_t that changes the global worker size of the kernel according to its contents. In this function it should contain only one element. The rest of the values are ignored.
  • buffers_size: A vector of size_t that changes the size of the buffers used to communicate with the kernel according to its contents. In this function it should contain only one element. The rest of the values are ignored.
  • multi_dimensional: A boolean that states if the kernel is multidimensional. By default, this parameter is set to false. Generally, if the multi_dimensional is true but global_work_size is empty, the default sizes of the buffers will be used. In this function this parameter is ignored.
Returns
A copy of the processed input.

Definition at line 862 of file ros_opencl.cpp.

std::vector< char > ros_opencl::ROS_OpenCL::process ( const std::vector< char >  v,
const std::vector< char >  v2,
const ROS_OpenCL_Params *  params = NULL 
)

The function that initiates kernel processing.

It uses a read/write buffer to send and receive data from the kernel for the first vector and a write only buffer for the second. The global work size used by default, matches the size of the first input vector. The size of the read/write buffer is typeof(char) * <input v size>. The size of the write only buffer is typeof(char) * <input v2 size>.

Parameters
vThe input data.
v2Secondary input data. Could be a small set of complementary values, or a full-scale dataset to be compared with v.
paramsoptional A ROS_OpenCL_Params object that includes the following params:
  • global_work_size: A vector of size_t that changes the global worker size of the kernel according to its contents. In this function it should contain a maximum of two elements. The rest of the values are ignored.
  • buffers_size: A vector of size_t that changes the size of the buffers used to communicate with the kernel according to its contents. In this function it should contain only two elements. The rest of the values are ignored.
  • multi_dimensional: A boolean that states if the kernel is multidimensional. By default, this parameter is set to false. Generally, if the multi_dimensional is true but global_work_size is empty, the default sizes of the buffers will be used. If global_work_size is not empty, the value of multi_dimensional is ignored with a warning.
Returns
A copy of the processed input based on v.

Definition at line 912 of file ros_opencl.cpp.

void ros_opencl::ROS_OpenCL::process ( std::vector< char > *  v,
const std::vector< char >  v2,
const ROS_OpenCL_Params *  params = NULL 
)

The function that initiates kernel processing.

It uses a read/write buffer to send and receive data from the kernel for the first vector and a write only buffer for the second. The global work size used by default, matches the size of the first input vector. The size of the read/write buffer is typeof(char) * <input v size>. The size of the write only buffer is typeof(char) * <input v2 size>. Changes made inside the kernel are overwritten on v.

Parameters
vThe input data.
v2Secondary input data. Could be a small set of complementary values, or a full-scale dataset to be compared with v.
paramsoptional A ROS_OpenCL_Params object that includes the following params:
  • global_work_size: A vector of size_t that changes the global worker size of the kernel according to its contents. In this function it should contain a maximum of two elements. The rest of the values are ignored.
  • buffers_size: A vector of size_t that changes the size of the buffers used to communicate with the kernel according to its contents. In this function it should contain only two elements. The rest of the values are ignored.
  • multi_dimensional: A boolean that states if the kernel is multidimensional. By default, this parameter is set to false. Generally, if the multi_dimensional is true but global_work_size is empty, the default sizes of the buffers will be used. If global_work_size is not empty, the value of multi_dimensional is ignored with a warning.

The size of the read/write buffers is typeof(int) * <input v size> and typeof(float) * <input v2 size>. Changes made inside the kernel are overwritten on both v and v2 respectively.

Parameters
vThe input data.
v2Secondary input data. Could be a small set of complementary values, or a full-scale dataset to be compared with v.
paramsoptional A ROS_OpenCL_Params object that includes the following params:
  • global_work_size: A vector of size_t that changes the global worker size of the kernel according to its contents. In this function it should contain a maximum of two elements. The rest of the values are ignored.
  • buffers_size: A vector of size_t that changes the size of the buffers used to communicate with the kernel according to its contents. In this function it should contain only two elements. The rest of the values are ignored.
  • multi_dimensional: A boolean that states if the kernel is multidimensional. By default, this parameter is set to false. Generally, if the multi_dimensional is true but global_work_size is empty, the default sizes of the buffers will be used. If global_work_size is not empty, the value of multi_dimensional is ignored with a warning.

  • global_work_size: A vector of size_t that changes the global worker size of the kernel according to its contents. In this function it should contain a maximum of two elements. The rest of the values are ignored.
  • buffers_size: A vector of size_t that changes the size of the buffers used to communicate with the kernel according to its contents. In this function it should contain only two elements. The rest of the values are ignored.
  • multi_dimensional: A boolean that states if the kernel is multidimensional. By default, this parameter is set to false. Generally, if the multi_dimensional is true but global_work_size is empty, the default sizes of the buffers will be used. If global_work_size is not empty, the value of multi_dimensional is ignored with a warning.
Returns
A copy of the processed input based on v.

Definition at line 4044 of file ros_opencl.cpp.

void ros_opencl::ROS_OpenCL::process ( std::vector< double > *  v,
const std::vector< int >  v2,
const ROS_OpenCL_Params *  params = NULL 
)

The function that initiates kernel processing.

It uses a read/write buffer to send and receive data from the kernel for the first vector and a write only buffer for the second. The global work size used by default, matches the size of the first input vector. The size of the read/write buffer is typeof(double) * <input v size>. The size of the write only buffer is typeof(int) * <input v2 size>. Changes made inside the kernel are overwritten only on v.

  • global_work_size: A vector of size_t that changes the global worker size of the kernel according to its contents. In this function it should contain a maximum of two elements. The rest of the values are ignored.
  • buffers_size: A vector of size_t that changes the size of the buffers used to communicate with the kernel according to its contents. In this function it should contain only two elements. The rest of the values are ignored.
  • multi_dimensional: A boolean that states if the kernel is multidimensional. By default, this parameter is set to false. Generally, if the multi_dimensional is true but global_work_size is empty, the default sizes of the buffers will be used. If global_work_size is not empty, the value of multi_dimensional is ignored with a warning.

Definition at line 5702 of file ros_opencl.cpp.

void ros_opencl::ROS_OpenCL::process ( std::vector< char > *  v,
std::vector< char > *  v2,
const std::vector< float >  v3,
const ROS_OpenCL_Params *  params = NULL 
)

The function that initiates kernel processing.

It uses a read/write buffer to send and receive data from the kernel for the first and second vector and a write only buffer for the third. The global work size used by default, matches the size of the first input vector. The size of the read/write buffers is typeof(char) * <input v size> and typeof(char) * <input v2 size>. The size of the write only buffer is typeof(float) * <input v3 size>. Changes made inside the kernel are overwritten on both v and v2 respectively.

Parameters
vThe input data.
v2Secondary input data. Could be a small set of complementary values, or a full-scale dataset to be compared with v.
v3Extra input data. Could be a small set of complementary values, or a full-scale dataset.
paramsoptional A ROS_OpenCL_Params object that includes the following params:
  • global_work_size: A vector of size_t that changes the global worker size of the kernel according to its contents. In this function it should contain a maximum of two elements. The rest of the values are ignored.

Generally, if the multi_dimensional is true but global_work_size is empty, the default sizes of the buffers will be used. If global_work_size is not empty, the value of multi_dimensional is ignored with a warning.

  • buffers_size: A vector of size_t that changes the size of the buffers used to communicate with the kernel according to its contents. In this function it should contain only two elements. The rest of the values are ignored.
  • multi_dimensional: A boolean that states if the kernel is multidimensional. By default, this parameter is set to false. Generally, if the multi_dimensional is true but global_work_size is empty, the default sizes of the buffers will be used. If global_work_size is not empty, the value of multi_dimensional is ignored with a warning.

Definition at line 7470 of file ros_opencl.cpp.

void ros_opencl::ROS_OpenCL::process ( std::vector< char > *  v,
std::vector< int > *  v2,
std::vector< float > *  v3,
const ROS_OpenCL_Params *  params = NULL 
)

The function that initiates kernel processing.

It uses a read/write buffer to send and receive data from the kernel for the first, second and third vector. The global work size used by default, matches the size of the first input vector. The size of the read/write buffers is typeof(char) * <input v size>, typeof(int) * <input v2 size> and typeof(float) * <input v3 size>. Changes made inside the kernel are overwritten on all three vectors.

Parameters
vThe input data.
v2Secondary input data. Could be a small set of complementary values, or a full-scale dataset to be compared with v.
v3Extra input data. Could be a small set of complementary values, or a full-scale dataset.
paramsoptional A ROS_OpenCL_Params object that includes the following params:
  • global_work_size: A vector of size_t that changes the global worker size of the kernel according to its contents. In this function it should contain a maximum of two elements. The rest of the values are ignored.

Generally, if the multi_dimensional is true but global_work_size is empty, the default sizes of the buffers will be used. If global_work_size is not empty, the value of multi_dimensional is ignored with a warning.

Generally, if the multi_dimensional is true but global_work_size is empty, the default sizes of the buffers will be used. If global_work_size is not empty, the value of multi_dimensional is ignored with a warning.

Definition at line 9248 of file ros_opencl.cpp.

std::vector< char > ros_opencl::ROS_OpenCL::process ( const std::vector< char >  v,
const std::vector< float >  v2,
const std::vector< double >  v3,
const ROS_OpenCL_Params *  params = NULL 
)

The function that initiates kernel processing.

It uses a read/write buffer to send and receive data from the kernel for the first vector and a write only buffer for the second and third. The global work size used by default, matches the size of the first input vector. The size of the read/write buffer is typeof(char) * <input v size>. The size of the write only buffers are typeof(float) * <input v2 size> and typeof(double) * <input v3 size>.

Parameters
vThe input data.
v2Secondary input data. Could be a small set of complementary values, or a full-scale dataset.
v3Extra input data. Could be a small set of complementary values, or a full-scale dataset.
paramsoptional A ROS_OpenCL_Params object that includes the following params:
  • global_work_size: A vector of size_t that changes the global worker size of the kernel according to its contents. In this function it should contain a maximum of three elements. The rest of the values are ignored.
  • buffers_size: A vector of size_t that changes the size of the buffers used to communicate with the kernel according to its contents. In this function it should contain only two elements. The rest of the values are ignored.
  • multi_dimensional: A boolean that states if the kernel is multidimensional. By default, this parameter is set to false. Generally, if the multi_dimensional is true but global_work_size is empty, the default sizes of the buffers will be used. If global_work_size is not empty, the value of multi_dimensional is ignored with a warning.
Returns
A copy of the processed input based on v.

Definition at line 11041 of file ros_opencl.cpp.

void ros_opencl::ROS_OpenCL::process ( std::vector< char > *  v,
const std::vector< double >  v2,
const std::vector< double >  v3,
const ROS_OpenCL_Params *  params = NULL 
)

The function that initiates kernel processing.

It uses a read/write buffer to send and receive data from the kernel for the first vector and a write only buffer for the second and third. The global work size used by default, matches the size of the first input vector. The size of the read/write buffer is typeof(char) * <input v size>. The size of the write only buffers is typeof(double) * <input v2 size> and typeof(double) * <input v3 size>. Changes made inside the kernel are overwritten only on v.

Parameters
vThe input data.
v2Secondary input data. Could be a small set of complementary values, or a full-scale dataset to be compared with v.
v3Extra input data. Could be a small set of complementary values, or a full-scale dataset.
paramsoptional A ROS_OpenCL_Params object that includes the following params:
  • global_work_size: A vector of size_t that changes the global worker size of the kernel according to its contents. In this function it should contain a maximum of two elements. The rest of the values are ignored.
  • buffers_size: A vector of size_t that changes the size of the buffers used to communicate with the kernel according to its contents. In this function it should contain only two elements. The rest of the values are ignored.
  • multi_dimensional: A boolean that states if the kernel is multidimensional. By default, this parameter is set to false. Generally, if the multi_dimensional is true but global_work_size is empty, the default sizes of the buffers will be used. If global_work_size is not empty, the value of multi_dimensional is ignored with a warning.

It uses a read/write buffer to send and receive data from the kernel for the first and second vector and a write only buffer for the third. The global work size used by default, matches the size of the first input vector. The size of the read/write buffers is typeof(int) * <input v size> and typeof(char) * <input v2 size>. The size of the write only buffer is typeof(double) * <input v3 size>. Changes made inside the kernel are overwritten on both v and v2 respectively.

Parameters
vThe input data.
v2Secondary input data. Could be a small set of complementary values, or a full-scale dataset to be compared with v.
v3Extra input data. Could be a small set of complementary values, or a full-scale dataset.
paramsoptional A ROS_OpenCL_Params object that includes the following params:
  • global_work_size: A vector of size_t that changes the global worker size of the kernel according to its contents. In this function it should contain a maximum of two elements. The rest of the values are ignored.
  • buffers_size: A vector of size_t that changes the size of the buffers used to communicate with the kernel according to its contents. In this function it should contain only two elements. The rest of the values are ignored.
  • multi_dimensional: A boolean that states if the kernel is multidimensional. By default, this parameter is set to false. Generally, if the multi_dimensional is true but global_work_size is empty, the default sizes of the buffers will be used. If global_work_size is not empty, the value of multi_dimensional is ignored with a warning.

v2Secondary input data. Could be a small set of complementary values, or a full-scale dataset to be compared with v.
v3Extra input data. Could be a small set of complementary values, or a full-scale dataset.
paramsoptional A ROS_OpenCL_Params object that includes the following params:
  • global_work_size: A vector of size_t that changes the global worker size of the kernel according to its contents. In this function it should contain a maximum of two elements. The rest of the values are ignored.
  • buffers_size: A vector of size_t that changes the size of the buffers used to communicate with the kernel according to its contents. In this function it should contain only two elements. The rest of the values are ignored.
  • multi_dimensional: A boolean that states if the kernel is multidimensional. By default, this parameter is set to false. Generally, if the multi_dimensional is true but global_work_size is empty, the default sizes of the buffers will be used. If global_work_size is not empty, the value of multi_dimensional is ignored with a warning.

Definition at line 14682 of file ros_opencl.cpp.

std::vector< int > ros_opencl::ROS_OpenCL::process ( const std::vector< int >  v,
const std::vector< float >  v2,
const std::vector< char >  v3,
const ROS_OpenCL_Params *  params = NULL 
)

The function that initiates kernel processing.

It uses a read/write buffer to send and receive data from the kernel for the first vector and a write only buffer for the second and third. The global work size used by default, matches the size of the first input vector. The size of the read/write buffer is typeof(int) * <input v size>. The size of the write only buffers are typeof(float) * <input v2 size> and typeof(char) * <input v3 size>.

Parameters
vThe input data.
v2Secondary input data. Could be a small set of complementary values, or a full-scale dataset.
v3Extra input data. Could be a small set of complementary values, or a full-scale dataset.

  • multi_dimensional: A boolean that states if the kernel is multidimensional. By default, this parameter is set to false. Generally, if the multi_dimensional is true but global_work_size is empty, the default sizes of the buffers will be used. If global_work_size is not empty, the value of multi_dimensional is ignored with a warning.

  • buffers_size: A vector of size_t that changes the size of the buffers used to communicate with the kernel according to its contents. In this function it should contain only two elements. The rest of the values are ignored.
  • multi_dimensional: A boolean that states if the kernel is multidimensional. By default, this parameter is set to false. Generally, if the multi_dimensional is true but global_work_size is empty, the default sizes of the buffers will be used. If global_work_size is not empty, the value of multi_dimensional is ignored with a warning.
Returns
A copy of the processed input based on v.

Definition at line 16475 of file ros_opencl.cpp.

void ros_opencl::ROS_OpenCL::process ( std::vector< int > *  v,
const std::vector< double >  v2,
const std::vector< char >  v3,
const ROS_OpenCL_Params *  params = NULL 
)

The function that initiates kernel processing.

It uses a read/write buffer to send and receive data from the kernel for the first vector and a write only buffer for the second and third. The global work size used by default, matches the size of the first input vector. The size of the read/write buffer is typeof(int) * <input v size>. The size of the write only buffers is typeof(double) * <input v2 size> and typeof(char) * <input v3 size>. Changes made inside the kernel are overwritten only on v.

Parameters
vThe input data.
v2Secondary input data. Could be a small set of complementary values, or a full-scale dataset to be compared with v.
v3Extra input data. Could be a small set of complementary values, or a full-scale dataset.

  • global_work_size: A vector of size_t that changes the global worker size of the kernel according to its contents. In this function it should contain a maximum of two elements. The rest of the values are ignored.

  • multi_dimensional: A boolean that states if the kernel is multidimensional. By default, this parameter is set to false. Generally, if the multi_dimensional is true but global_work_size is empty, the default sizes of the buffers will be used. If global_work_size is not empty, the value of multi_dimensional is ignored with a warning.

Definition at line 18242 of file ros_opencl.cpp.

void ros_opencl::ROS_OpenCL::process ( std::vector< float > *  v,
std::vector< char > *  v2,
const std::vector< char >  v3,
const ROS_OpenCL_Params *  params = NULL 
)

The function that initiates kernel processing.

It uses a read/write buffer to send and receive data from the kernel for the first and second vector and a write only buffer for the third. The global work size used by default, matches the size of the first input vector. The size of the read/write buffers is typeof(float) * <input v size> and typeof(char) * <input v2 size>. The size of the write only buffer is typeof(char) * <input v3 size>. Changes made inside the kernel are overwritten on both v and v2 respectively.

Parameters
vThe input data.
v2Secondary input data. Could be a small set of complementary values, or a full-scale dataset to be compared with v.
v3Extra input data. Could be a small set of complementary values, or a full-scale dataset.
paramsoptional A ROS_OpenCL_Params object that includes the following params:
  • global_work_size: A vector of size_t that changes the global worker size of the kernel according to its contents. In this function it should contain a maximum of two elements. The rest of the values are ignored.
  • buffers_size: A vector of size_t that changes the size of the buffers used to communicate with the kernel according to its contents. In this function it should contain only two elements. The rest of the values are ignored.
  • multi_dimensional: A boolean that states if the kernel is multidimensional. By default, this parameter is set to false. Generally, if the multi_dimensional is true but global_work_size is empty, the default sizes of the buffers will be used. If global_work_size is not empty, the value of multi_dimensional is ignored with a warning.

Generally, if the multi_dimensional is true but global_work_size is empty, the default sizes of the buffers will be used. If global_work_size is not empty, the value of multi_dimensional is ignored with a warning.

Definition at line 20010 of file ros_opencl.cpp.

void ros_opencl::ROS_OpenCL::process ( std::vector< float > *  v,
std::vector< int > *  v2,
std::vector< char > *  v3,
const ROS_OpenCL_Params *  params = NULL 
)

The function that initiates kernel processing.

It uses a read/write buffer to send and receive data from the kernel for the first, second and third vector. The global work size used by default, matches the size of the first input vector. The size of the read/write buffers is typeof(float) * <input v size>, typeof(int) * <input v2 size> and typeof(char) * <input v3 size>. Changes made inside the kernel are overwritten on all three vectors.

Parameters
vThe input data.
v2Secondary input data. Could be a small set of complementary values, or a full-scale dataset to be compared with v.
v3Extra input data. Could be a small set of complementary values, or a full-scale dataset.
paramsoptional A ROS_OpenCL_Params object that includes the following params:
  • global_work_size: A vector of size_t that changes the global worker size of the kernel according to its contents. In this function it should contain a maximum of two elements. The rest of the values are ignored.
  • buffers_size: A vector of size_t that changes the size of the buffers used to communicate with the kernel according to its contents. In this function it should contain only two elements. The rest of the values are ignored.
  • multi_dimensional: A boolean that states if the kernel is multidimensional. By default, this parameter is set to false. Generally, if the multi_dimensional is true but global_work_size is empty, the default sizes of the buffers will be used. If global_work_size is not empty, the value of multi_dimensional is ignored with a warning.

std::vector< float > ros_opencl::ROS_OpenCL::process ( const std::vector< float >  v,
const std::vector< float >  v2,
const std::vector< int >  v3,
const ROS_OpenCL_Params *  params = NULL 
)

The function that initiates kernel processing.

It uses a read/write buffer to send and receive data from the kernel for the first vector and a write only buffer for the second and third. The global work size used by default, matches the size of the first input vector. The size of the read/write buffer is typeof(float) * <input v size>. The size of the write only buffers are typeof(float) * <input v2 size> and typeof(int) * <input v3 size>.

Parameters
vThe input data.
v2Secondary input data. Could be a small set of complementary values, or a full-scale dataset.
v3Extra input data. Could be a small set of complementary values, or a full-scale dataset.
paramsoptional A ROS_OpenCL_Params object that includes the following params:
  • global_work_size: A vector of size_t that changes the global worker size of the kernel according to its contents. In this function it should contain a maximum of three elements. The rest of the values are ignored.
  • buffers_size: A vector of size_t that changes the size of the buffers used to communicate with the kernel according to its contents. In this function it should contain only two elements. The rest of the values are ignored.
  • multi_dimensional: A boolean that states if the kernel is multidimensional. By default, this parameter is set to false. Generally, if the multi_dimensional is true but global_work_size is empty, the default sizes of the buffers will be used. If global_work_size is not empty, the value of multi_dimensional is ignored with a warning.
Returns
A copy of the processed input based on v.

It uses a read/write buffer to send and receive data from the kernel for the first vector and a write only buffer for the second and third. The global work size used by default, matches the size of the first input vector. The size of the read/write buffer is typeof(float) * <input v size>. The size of the write only buffers is typeof(double) * <input v2 size> and typeof(int) * <input v3 size>. Changes made inside the kernel are overwritten only on v.

Parameters
vThe input data.
v2Secondary input data. Could be a small set of complementary values, or a full-scale dataset to be compared with v.
v3Extra input data. Could be a small set of complementary values, or a full-scale dataset.
paramsoptional A ROS_OpenCL_Params object that includes the following params:
  • global_work_size: A vector of size_t that changes the global worker size of the kernel according to its contents. In this function it should contain a maximum of two elements. The rest of the values are ignored.
  • buffers_size: A vector of size_t that changes the size of the buffers used to communicate with the kernel according to its contents. In this function it should contain only two elements. The rest of the values are ignored.
  • multi_dimensional: A boolean that states if the kernel is multidimensional. By default, this parameter is set to false. Generally, if the multi_dimensional is true but global_work_size is empty, the default sizes of the buffers will be used. If global_work_size is not empty, the value of multi_dimensional is ignored with a warning.

vThe input data.
v2Secondary input data. Could be a small set of complementary values, or a full-scale dataset to be compared with v.
v3Extra input data. Could be a small set of complementary values, or a full-scale dataset.
paramsoptional A ROS_OpenCL_Params object that includes the following params:
  • global_work_size: A vector of size_t that changes the global worker size of the kernel according to its contents. In this function it should contain a maximum of two elements. The rest of the values are ignored.
  • buffers_size: A vector of size_t that changes the size of the buffers used to communicate with the kernel according to its contents. In this function it should contain only two elements. The rest of the values are ignored.
  • multi_dimensional: A boolean that states if the kernel is multidimensional. By default, this parameter is set to false. Generally, if the multi_dimensional is true but global_work_size is empty, the default sizes of the buffers will be used. If global_work_size is not empty, the value of multi_dimensional is ignored with a warning.

  • global_work_size: A vector of size_t that changes the global worker size of the kernel according to its contents. In this function it should contain a maximum of two elements. The rest of the values are ignored.
  • buffers_size: A vector of size_t that changes the size of the buffers used to communicate with the kernel according to its contents. In this function it should contain only two elements. The rest of the values are ignored.
  • multi_dimensional: A boolean that states if the kernel is multidimensional. By default, this parameter is set to false. Generally, if the multi_dimensional is true but global_work_size is empty, the default sizes of the buffers will be used. If global_work_size is not empty, the value of multi_dimensional is ignored with a warning.

Definition at line 27222 of file ros_opencl.cpp.

std::vector< double > ros_opencl::ROS_OpenCL::process ( const std::vector< double >  v,
const std::vector< int >  v2,
const std::vector< float >  v3,
const ROS_OpenCL_Params *  params = NULL 
)

The function that initiates kernel processing.

It uses a read/write buffer to send and receive data from the kernel for the first vector and a write only buffer for the second and third. The global work size used by default, matches the size of the first input vector. The size of the read/write buffer is typeof(double) * <input v size>. The size of the write only buffers are typeof(int) * <input v2 size> and typeof(float) * <input v3 size>.

Parameters
vThe input data.
v2Secondary input data. Could be a small set of complementary values, or a full-scale dataset.

  • multi_dimensional: A boolean that states if the kernel is multidimensional. By default, this parameter is set to false. Generally, if the multi_dimensional is true but global_work_size is empty, the default sizes of the buffers will be used. If global_work_size is not empty, the value of multi_dimensional is ignored with a warning.
Returns
A copy of the processed input based on v.

Definition at line 29015 of file ros_opencl.cpp.

void ros_opencl::ROS_OpenCL::process ( std::vector< double > *  v,
const std::vector< float >  v2,
const std::vector< float >  v3,
const ROS_OpenCL_Params *  params = NULL 
)

The function that initiates kernel processing.

It uses a read/write buffer to send and receive data from the kernel for the first vector and a write only buffer for the second and third. The global work size used by default, matches the size of the first input vector. The size of the read/write buffer is typeof(double) * <input v size>. The size of the write only buffers is typeof(float) * <input v2 size> and typeof(float) * <input v3 size>. Changes made inside the kernel are overwritten only on v.

Parameters
vThe input data.
v2Secondary input data. Could be a small set of complementary values, or a full-scale dataset to be compared with v.
v3Extra input data. Could be a small set of complementary values, or a full-scale dataset.
paramsoptional A ROS_OpenCL_Params object that includes the following params:
  • global_work_size: A vector of size_t that changes the global worker size of the kernel according to its contents. In this function it should contain a maximum of two elements. The rest of the values are ignored.
  • buffers_size: A vector of size_t that changes the size of the buffers used to communicate with the kernel according to its contents. In this function it should contain only two elements. The rest of the values are ignored.

Generally, if the multi_dimensional is true but global_work_size is empty, the default sizes of the buffers will be used. If global_work_size is not empty, the value of multi_dimensional is ignored with a warning.

  • multi_dimensional: A boolean that states if the kernel is multidimensional. By default, this parameter is set to false. Generally, if the multi_dimensional is true but global_work_size is empty, the default sizes of the buffers will be used. If global_work_size is not empty, the value of multi_dimensional is ignored with a warning.

Definition at line 30782 of file ros_opencl.cpp.

void ros_opencl::ROS_OpenCL::process ( std::vector< double > *  v,
std::vector< double > *  v2,
const std::vector< float >  v3,
const ROS_OpenCL_Params *  params = NULL 
)

The function that initiates kernel processing.

It uses a read/write buffer to send and receive data from the kernel for the first and second vector and a write only buffer for the third. The global work size used by default, matches the size of the first input vector. The size of the read/write buffers is typeof(double) * <input v size> and typeof(double) * <input v2 size>. The size of the write only buffer is typeof(float) * <input v3 size>. Changes made inside the kernel are overwritten on both v and v2 respectively.

Parameters
vThe input data.
v2Secondary input data. Could be a small set of complementary values, or a full-scale dataset to be compared with v.
v3Extra input data. Could be a small set of complementary values, or a full-scale dataset.
paramsoptional A ROS_OpenCL_Params object that includes the following params:
  • global_work_size: A vector of size_t that changes the global worker size of the kernel according to its contents. In this function it should contain a maximum of two elements. The rest of the values are ignored.
  • buffers_size: A vector of size_t that changes the size of the buffers used to communicate with the kernel according to its contents. In this function it should contain only two elements. The rest of the values are ignored.
  • multi_dimensional: A boolean that states if the kernel is multidimensional. By default, this parameter is set to false. Generally, if the multi_dimensional is true but global_work_size is empty, the default sizes of the buffers will be used. If global_work_size is not empty, the value of multi_dimensional is ignored with a warning.
